# CODEOWNERS — enforced trust boundary for the verified core (steering Phase 4, R-C5).
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS
# --------------------
# The Lean kernel is a non-gameable correctness oracle, but it cannot catch a
# *weakened* theorem statement, a loosened verifier config, or a regressed
# conformance floor (see docs/agent-progress-steering-review.md §3 G1.1/G2.3).
# Those edits live in a well-defined set of files. CODEOWNERS designates a
# human owner for exactly that set so the change cannot merge without a
# maintainer's eyes on it.
#
# CODEOWNERS ALONE IS ADVISORY. It only *requests* review from the listed
# owner. It becomes an enforced merge gate only when paired with a branch
# protection / repository **ruleset** that turns on "Require review from Code
# Owners". The companion ruleset is a repo *setting* (not a file in the repo)
# and must be configured by the maintainer in the GitHub UI / API. The Phase 4
# PR body lists the proposed ruleset and the open question on approval counts.
#
# INTENDED RULESET (proposed — see Phase 4 PR open questions)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
#   * Verified core (the paths below): require Code Owner review.
#       2 approvals once there is >1 maintainer; 1 approval today
#       (single-maintainer repo). Tracks report R-C5 / open question #1.
#   * Codegen + everything else: deliberately NOT owned here, so it carries
#       the lighter bar (no Code-Owner gate). The RISC-V lowering / ziskemu
#       path is unverified by design (report §6) — it is fenced by conformance
#       + fuzz + dual-path checks, not by the kernel, so a Code-Owner review
#       requirement buys less there and would just bottleneck the maintainer.
#
# Last matching pattern wins (gitignore semantics). Order matters.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Progress registry — the kernel-checked source of truth for every tier count,
# obligation, and witness abbrev. A silent tier flip or a vacuous witness here
# is the highest-signal drift in the repo.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/EvmAsm/Progress.lean              @pirapira
/EvmAsm/Progress/                  @pirapira

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RV64 model — the trusted machine semantics every codegen proof reduces to.
# A change to Instr semantics in Rv64/Basic.lean re-bases the whole proof core.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/EvmAsm/Rv64/                      @pirapira

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Spec / statement files — the Hoare-triple statements the kernel proves. The
# kernel guarantees the proof is valid; it cannot guarantee the *statement*
# says what we claim. Editing a Spec.lean is editing what "proven" means.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/Spec.lean                       @pirapira

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Conformance vectors — the kernel-checked EVM-semantics ground truth. Silent
# vector deletion lowers the floor; check-conformance-floor.sh ratchets it, but
# the statements themselves are trust-core.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/EvmAsm/EL/Conformance/            @pirapira

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Verifier configuration — files that change what "passing" *means*: the CI
# gate scripts, the conformance/axiom/EEST-tag registries, the EEST harness,
# the build toolchain. (Mirrors the set in scripts/check-statement-tamper.sh.)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/lakefile.toml                     @pirapira
/lean-toolchain                    @pirapira
/scripts/check-*.sh                @pirapira
/scripts/axiom-allow.txt           @pirapira
/scripts/conformance-baseline.txt  @pirapira
/scripts/eest-fixture-tag.txt      @pirapira
/scripts/codegen-eest-stateless-check.sh @pirapira
/scripts/progress-report.sh        @pirapira
/scripts/progress-snapshot.sh      @pirapira
/scripts/progress-velocity.sh      @pirapira
/scripts/progress-delta.sh         @pirapira

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CI workflows — a loosened workflow can disable a gate. Treat as trust-core.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/workflows/                @pirapira
/.github/CODEOWNERS                @pirapira
